<paragraph blockId="30.[151,1437,438,1400]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,510,536]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Gustafsson &amp; Bush, 2022" authorityName="Gustafsson &amp; Bush" authorityYear="2022" box="[329,790,510,536]" class="Insecta" family="Philopteridae" genus="Indoceoplanetes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Psocodea" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subarcens" status="new species" subGenus="Capnodella">
<emphasis box="[329,513,510,536]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Indoceoplanetes</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[530,661,510,536]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Capnodella</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[677,790,510,536]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">subarcens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[798,935,510,536]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[798,935,510,536]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is most similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Gustafsson &amp; Bush, 2022" authorityName="Gustafsson &amp; Bush" authorityYear="2022" box="[1147,1324,510,537]" class="Insecta" family="Philopteridae" genus="Indoceoplanetes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Psocodea" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="saucia" status="new species" subGenus="Capnodella">
<emphasis box="[1147,1178,511,536]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">In.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[1195,1234,511,537]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Cp.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[1251,1324,511,536]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">saucia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
<taxonomicNameLabel pageId="30" pageNumber="31" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
. For a comparison of these two species, see 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gustafsson &amp; Bush" authorityYear="2022" box="[693,909,546,573]" class="Insecta" family="Philopteridae" genus="Indoceoplanetes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Psocodea" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subarcens" subGenus="Capnodella">
<emphasis box="[693,724,547,572]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">In.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[740,780,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Cp.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[796,909,546,572]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">subarcens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, above.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="30" pageNumber="31" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="30.[151,1437,438,1400]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,485,582,609]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
Description. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[353,479,582,609]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Both sexes</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Head flat dome-shaped (
<figureCitation box="[773,858,582,608]" captionStart="FIGURES 73–82. 73" captionStartId="34.[151,264,1783,1807]" captionTargetBox="[254,1333,193,1750]" captionTargetId="figure-23@34.[236,1352,181,1759]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="FIGURES 73–82. 73, Indoceoplanetes (Capnodella) saucia n. sp. ex Edolisoma montanum montanum, male head, dorsal and ventral views. 74–82. Male Genitalia. Indoceoplanetes (Capnodella) kamphaengphetensis n. sp. ex Lalage melaschistos avensis: 74, dorsal view. 75, male mesosome, ventral view. 76, male paramere, dorsal view. Indoceoplanetes (Capnodella) subarcens n. sp. ex Edolisoma melas melas: 77, dorsal view. 78, male mesosome, ventral view. 79, male paramere, dorsal view. Indoceoplanetes (Capnodella) saucia n. sp. ex Edolisoma montanum montanum: 80, dorsal view. 81, male mesosome, ventral view. 82, male paramere, dorsal view. Abbreviations: ames = anterior mesosomal seta; gpmes = gonoporal posterior mesosomal seta; lpmes = lateral posterior mesosomal seta; pst1–2 = parameral setae 1–2." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825597" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825597/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Fig. 73</figureCitation>
), lateral margins of preantennal area convex, frons rounded. Marginal carina broad, narrowing conspicuously near 
<emphasis box="[867,923,618,644]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">dsms</emphasis>
, interrupted submedianly. Dorsal preantennal suture reaches 
<emphasis box="[319,375,654,680]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">dsms</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis box="[431,470,654,680]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">ads</emphasis>
, and continues median to 
<emphasis box="[767,806,654,680]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">ads</emphasis>
, but not completely separating dorsal anterior plate and not reaching lateral head margins. Dorsal anterior plate about as broad as long, with sinuous thickening in posterior half. Ventral anterior plate rounded triangular. Head chaetotaxy as in 
<figureCitation box="[929,1012,726,752]" captionStart="FIGURES 73–82. 73" captionStartId="34.[151,264,1783,1807]" captionTargetBox="[254,1333,193,1750]" captionTargetId="figure-23@34.[236,1352,181,1759]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="FIGURES 73–82. 73, Indoceoplanetes (Capnodella) saucia n. sp. ex Edolisoma montanum montanum, male head, dorsal and ventral views. 74–82. Male Genitalia. Indoceoplanetes (Capnodella) kamphaengphetensis n. sp. ex Lalage melaschistos avensis: 74, dorsal view. 75, male mesosome, ventral view. 76, male paramere, dorsal view. Indoceoplanetes (Capnodella) subarcens n. sp. ex Edolisoma melas melas: 77, dorsal view. 78, male mesosome, ventral view. 79, male paramere, dorsal view. Indoceoplanetes (Capnodella) saucia n. sp. ex Edolisoma montanum montanum: 80, dorsal view. 81, male mesosome, ventral view. 82, male paramere, dorsal view. Abbreviations: ames = anterior mesosomal seta; gpmes = gonoporal posterior mesosomal seta; lpmes = lateral posterior mesosomal seta; pst1–2 = parameral setae 1–2." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825597" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825597/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Fig. 73</figureCitation>
. Preantennal nodi large, bulging. Pre- and postocular nodi of similar size. Marginal temporal carina of moderate width. Gular plate with rounded lateral margins converging on median point. Thoracic and abdominal segments as in 
<figureCitation box="[1025,1154,798,824]" captionStart="FIGURES 66–67" captionStartId="31.[151,264,1927,1951]" captionTargetBox="[227,1387,201,1892]" captionTargetId="figure-17@31.[151,1436,181,1904]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="FIGURES 66–67. Indoceoplanetes (Capnodella) saucia n. sp. ex Edolisoma montanum montanum. 66, male habitus, dorsal and ventral views. 67, female habitus, dorsal and ventral views." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825591" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825591/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Figs 66–67</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="30.[151,1437,438,1400]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,265,834,861]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Male.</emphasis>
Thoracic and abdominal chaetotaxy as in 
<figureCitation box="[752,836,834,860]" captionStart="FIGURES 66–67" captionStartId="31.[151,264,1927,1951]" captionTargetBox="[227,1387,201,1892]" captionTargetId="figure-17@31.[151,1436,181,1904]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="FIGURES 66–67. Indoceoplanetes (Capnodella) saucia n. sp. ex Edolisoma montanum montanum. 66, male habitus, dorsal and ventral views. 67, female habitus, dorsal and ventral views." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825591" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825591/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Fig. 66</figureCitation>
; segment IV with 2 
<emphasis box="[1072,1097,835,860]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">ps</emphasis>
on each side. Basal apodeme slender, lateral margins slightly concave in proximal section, bulging markedly in distal section (
<figureCitation box="[1231,1315,870,896]" captionStart="FIGURES 73–82. 73" captionStartId="34.[151,264,1783,1807]" captionTargetBox="[254,1333,193,1750]" captionTargetId="figure-23@34.[236,1352,181,1759]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="FIGURES 73–82. 73, Indoceoplanetes (Capnodella) saucia n. sp. ex Edolisoma montanum montanum, male head, dorsal and ventral views. 74–82. Male Genitalia. Indoceoplanetes (Capnodella) kamphaengphetensis n. sp. ex Lalage melaschistos avensis: 74, dorsal view. 75, male mesosome, ventral view. 76, male paramere, dorsal view. Indoceoplanetes (Capnodella) subarcens n. sp. ex Edolisoma melas melas: 77, dorsal view. 78, male mesosome, ventral view. 79, male paramere, dorsal view. Indoceoplanetes (Capnodella) saucia n. sp. ex Edolisoma montanum montanum: 80, dorsal view. 81, male mesosome, ventral view. 82, male paramere, dorsal view. Abbreviations: ames = anterior mesosomal seta; gpmes = gonoporal posterior mesosomal seta; lpmes = lateral posterior mesosomal seta; pst1–2 = parameral setae 1–2." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825597" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825597/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Fig. 80</figureCitation>
). Proximal mesosome rounded (
<figureCitation box="[383,466,906,932]" captionStart="FIGURES 73–82. 73" captionStartId="34.[151,264,1783,1807]" captionTargetBox="[254,1333,193,1750]" captionTargetId="figure-23@34.[236,1352,181,1759]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="FIGURES 73–82. 73, Indoceoplanetes (Capnodella) saucia n. sp. ex Edolisoma montanum montanum, male head, dorsal and ventral views. 74–82. Male Genitalia. Indoceoplanetes (Capnodella) kamphaengphetensis n. sp. ex Lalage melaschistos avensis: 74, dorsal view. 75, male mesosome, ventral view. 76, male paramere, dorsal view. Indoceoplanetes (Capnodella) subarcens n. sp. ex Edolisoma melas melas: 77, dorsal view. 78, male mesosome, ventral view. 79, male paramere, dorsal view. Indoceoplanetes (Capnodella) saucia n. sp. ex Edolisoma montanum montanum: 80, dorsal view. 81, male mesosome, ventral view. 82, male paramere, dorsal view. Abbreviations: ames = anterior mesosomal seta; gpmes = gonoporal posterior mesosomal seta; lpmes = lateral posterior mesosomal seta; pst1–2 = parameral setae 1–2." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825597" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825597/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Fig. 80</figureCitation>
), in some specimens slightly narrowed medianly (
<figureCitation box="[1026,1109,906,932]" captionStart="FIGURES 73–82. 73" captionStartId="34.[151,264,1783,1807]" captionTargetBox="[254,1333,193,1750]" captionTargetId="figure-23@34.[236,1352,181,1759]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="FIGURES 73–82. 73, Indoceoplanetes (Capnodella) saucia n. sp. ex Edolisoma montanum montanum, male head, dorsal and ventral views. 74–82. Male Genitalia. Indoceoplanetes (Capnodella) kamphaengphetensis n. sp. ex Lalage melaschistos avensis: 74, dorsal view. 75, male mesosome, ventral view. 76, male paramere, dorsal view. Indoceoplanetes (Capnodella) subarcens n. sp. ex Edolisoma melas melas: 77, dorsal view. 78, male mesosome, ventral view. 79, male paramere, dorsal view. Indoceoplanetes (Capnodella) saucia n. sp. ex Edolisoma montanum montanum: 80, dorsal view. 81, male mesosome, ventral view. 82, male paramere, dorsal view. Abbreviations: ames = anterior mesosomal seta; gpmes = gonoporal posterior mesosomal seta; lpmes = lateral posterior mesosomal seta; pst1–2 = parameral setae 1–2." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825597" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825597/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Fig. 81</figureCitation>
). Mesosomal lobes narrowed laterally. Gonopore as in 
<figureCitation box="[428,509,942,968]" captionStart="FIGURES 73–82. 73" captionStartId="34.[151,264,1783,1807]" captionTargetBox="[254,1333,193,1750]" captionTargetId="figure-23@34.[236,1352,181,1759]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="FIGURES 73–82. 73, Indoceoplanetes (Capnodella) saucia n. sp. ex Edolisoma montanum montanum, male head, dorsal and ventral views. 74–82. Male Genitalia. Indoceoplanetes (Capnodella) kamphaengphetensis n. sp. ex Lalage melaschistos avensis: 74, dorsal view. 75, male mesosome, ventral view. 76, male paramere, dorsal view. Indoceoplanetes (Capnodella) subarcens n. sp. ex Edolisoma melas melas: 77, dorsal view. 78, male mesosome, ventral view. 79, male paramere, dorsal view. Indoceoplanetes (Capnodella) saucia n. sp. ex Edolisoma montanum montanum: 80, dorsal view. 81, male mesosome, ventral view. 82, male paramere, dorsal view. Abbreviations: ames = anterior mesosomal seta; gpmes = gonoporal posterior mesosomal seta; lpmes = lateral posterior mesosomal seta; pst1–2 = parameral setae 1–2." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825597" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825597/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Fig. 81</figureCitation>
; distal margin straight to slightly convex, antero-lateral extensions curved, rounded. Parameres with narrow heads; 
<emphasis box="[496,571,978,1004]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">pst1–2</emphasis>
as in 
<figureCitation box="[637,720,978,1004]" captionStart="FIGURES 73–82. 73" captionStartId="34.[151,264,1783,1807]" captionTargetBox="[254,1333,193,1750]" captionTargetId="figure-23@34.[236,1352,181,1759]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="FIGURES 73–82. 73, Indoceoplanetes (Capnodella) saucia n. sp. ex Edolisoma montanum montanum, male head, dorsal and ventral views. 74–82. Male Genitalia. Indoceoplanetes (Capnodella) kamphaengphetensis n. sp. ex Lalage melaschistos avensis: 74, dorsal view. 75, male mesosome, ventral view. 76, male paramere, dorsal view. Indoceoplanetes (Capnodella) subarcens n. sp. ex Edolisoma melas melas: 77, dorsal view. 78, male mesosome, ventral view. 79, male paramere, dorsal view. Indoceoplanetes (Capnodella) saucia n. sp. ex Edolisoma montanum montanum: 80, dorsal view. 81, male mesosome, ventral view. 82, male paramere, dorsal view. Abbreviations: ames = anterior mesosomal seta; gpmes = gonoporal posterior mesosomal seta; lpmes = lateral posterior mesosomal seta; pst1–2 = parameral setae 1–2." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825597" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825597/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Fig. 82</figureCitation>
. Measurements as in 
<tableCitation box="[959,1043,978,1004]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="47.[151,239,457,483]" captionText="TABLE 1. Measurements (in mm) of species treated in this paper. Abbreviations used: TL = total length; HL = head length (along midline); HW = head width (at temples); PRW = prothorax width; PTW = pterothorax width; AW = abdominal width (at segment V). Note: many specimens had distorted abdomens, as noted below; consequently, the TL of many specimens could not be measured. Mean values are given in parentheses only where 10 or more individuals were measured. N = number of specimens examined." pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Table 1</tableCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="30.[151,1437,438,1400]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,293,1014,1041]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Female.</emphasis>
Thoracic and abdominal chaetotaxy as in 
<figureCitation box="[768,850,1014,1040]" captionStart="FIGURES 66–67" captionStartId="31.[151,264,1927,1951]" captionTargetBox="[227,1387,201,1892]" captionTargetId="figure-17@31.[151,1436,181,1904]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="FIGURES 66–67. Indoceoplanetes (Capnodella) saucia n. sp. ex Edolisoma montanum montanum. 66, male habitus, dorsal and ventral views. 67, female habitus, dorsal and ventral views." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825591" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825591/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Fig. 67</figureCitation>
; segments IV–VI with 2 
<emphasis box="[1132,1157,1015,1040]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">ps</emphasis>
on each side. Subgenital plate rounded triangular (
<figureCitation box="[435,519,1050,1076]" captionStart="FIGURES 68–70. 68" captionStartId="32.[151,264,1854,1878]" captionTargetBox="[151,1429,195,1819]" captionTargetId="figure-23@32.[151,1436,181,1831]" captionTargetPageId="32" captionText="FIGURES 68–70. 68, Indoceoplanetes (Capnodella) kamphaengphetensis n. sp. ex Lalage melaschistos avensis, male habitus, dorsal and ventral views. 69, Indoceoplanetes (Capnodella) subarcens n. sp. ex Edolisoma melas melas, female subgenital plate and vulval margin, ventral view. 70, Indoceoplanetes (Capnodella) saucia n. sp. ex Edolisoma montanum montanum, female subgenital plate and vulval margin, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825593" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825593/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Fig. 70</figureCitation>
). Vulval margin gently rounded, with 0–1 short, slender 
<emphasis box="[1151,1195,1051,1076]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">vms</emphasis>
and 4–6 short, thornlike 
<emphasis box="[200,234,1087,1112]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">vss</emphasis>
on each side; 6–9 slender 
<emphasis box="[532,569,1087,1112]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">vos</emphasis>
on each side of subgenital plate; distal 2–3 
<emphasis box="[1061,1098,1087,1112]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">vos</emphasis>
positioned median to 
<emphasis box="[1347,1381,1087,1112]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">vss</emphasis>
, and markedly longer than 
<emphasis box="[398,442,1123,1148]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">vms</emphasis>
. Measurements as in 
<tableCitation box="[684,768,1122,1148]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="47.[151,239,457,483]" captionText="TABLE 1. Measurements (in mm) of species treated in this paper. Abbreviations used: TL = total length; HL = head length (along midline); HW = head width (at temples); PRW = prothorax width; PTW = pterothorax width; AW = abdominal width (at segment V). Note: many specimens had distorted abdomens, as noted below; consequently, the TL of many specimens could not be measured. Mean values are given in parentheses only where 10 or more individuals were measured. N = number of specimens examined." pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Table 1</tableCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="30" pageNumber="31" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="30.[151,1437,438,1400]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1158,1184]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species epithet is derived from Latin “ 
<emphasis box="[821,905,1159,1184]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">saucius</emphasis>
” for “ill”, referring to the pale pigmentation of this species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
